<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 03 at 3:31PM ADT  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will affect portions of Lajas, Cabo Rojo,
San German and Hormigueros Municipalities through 315 PM AST...
At 230 PM AST, a strong thunderstorm was over San German, moving
southwest at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 35 mph, frequent lightning and heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.
Locations impacted include...
Hormigueros, San German, Cabo Rojo, Lajas, Monte Grande, Puerto Real,
Palmarejo, Pole Ojea, Sabana Eneas, La Parguera and Betances.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
